# Steps to create a new virtual network

1. All Service -> Virtual networks -> create
  1. Basics tab
    a. Subscription: default
    b. Resource group: default
    c. Name: vnet1
    d. Region: East US
    e. Review + Create (validates)
    f. Create
    
 3. All services ->  Virtual machines -> create
  1. Basics tab
    a. Subscription: default
    b. Resource group: default
    c. Name: vm1
    d. Region: East US
    e. Image: Windows Server 2019 Datacenter - Gen2
    f. enter username and password
    g. public inbound ports: Allow selected ports
    h. selected inbound ports: RDP(3389)
   2. Networking tab
    a. choose create virtual network: vnet1
    b. public IP: autogenerated(vm1-ip)
    
 4. create another vm by following above steps
 5. choose vm1 -> overview ->  connect -> RDP
 6. disable private & public firwall in both vm's
 7. now we should be able to ping from one vm to another which are both on one virtual network
 
  

    
